Dangerous R Cookbook: ggplot2

The DRC is not for absolute R beginners. It assumes some familiarity with the language. It is intended for people who want to do things with R packages. 

The DRC philosophy is to use 1 set of methods to accomplish 90% of what you need. Each example shows 1 specific applicationof those methods. 

Packages are not explained, except to reveal underlying structures that make you more dangerous!  

There are quicker, simpler, and more elegant ways to accomplish specific R tasks; the DRC approach will quickly have you USING your R packages versatilely effectively. 


